The article discusses the water infrastructure challenges faced by the people of Jackson, Mississippi, and the efforts being made to address them. Last summer, a major flood worsened the existing problems in the water system, leaving many without water for days. The government recognizes the importance of clean, safe drinking water for all Americans and has directed resources to support Jackson. In December, legislation was signed to stabilize the city's water infrastructure, and now an initial investment of $115 million is being made to repair the system and ensure access to clean water. The government is also working on a broader plan to replace lead pipes, improve water quality, and strengthen the nation's drinking water infrastructure. The fight for clean water will continue until all children can safely drink from the tap. Congressman Bennie Thompson is acknowledged for his support and advocacy for the Jackson community.